The paper deals with wireless communications and structured coding, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a compression framework, which falls under the Compression (cs.CC) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents numerical results to demonstrate the performance of the proposed scheme, which could be considered as a Simulation and Modeling (cs.SI) sub-category.
